            "text": "{\"model\":\"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001\",\"id\":\"msg_01KD66PZ8ZEmSUhNw5sGUY4o\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"id\":\"toolu_01UBC9SySHiNjTw9YPK418tD\",\"name\":\"extract-10\",\"input\":{\"type\":\"helpMe\",\"text\":\"I love the concept! \\\"Friend of the Pod\\\" is a catchy name. But I need to understand your business model better so we can craft truly compelling marketing copy. Let me help you structure your answer with some specificity.\",\"template\":\"**Friend of the Pod is a podcast matchmaking service that:**\\n- Connects [WHO] with [WHO] (e.g., guests with podcast hosts, listeners with shows, etc.)\\n- Solves the problem of [SPECIFIC PAIN POINT]\\n- Works by [HOW IT WORKS - the mechanism/process]\\n- Makes money by [BUSINESS MODEL]\\n- Is different from competitors because [UNIQUE ANGLE/DIFFERENTIATION]\",\"examples\":[\"Example: Friend of the Pod connects indie podcast hosts with interesting guests. It solves the problem of hosts spending 20+ hours finding quality guests. It works through an AI-powered matching algorithm that analyzes host content and guest backgrounds. We make money through a subscription model ($99/month for unlimited matches). We're different because we focus exclusively on indie creators under 50k listeners, not big networks.\",\"Example: Friend of the Pod connects podcast listeners with shows they'll actually love. It solves listener overwhelm (there are 3M+ podcasts). It works by analyzing listening history and recommending personalized shows. We make money through affiliate revenue when listeners subscribe to premium feeds. We're different because our algorithm considers tone and pacing, not just topic.\"]}}],\"stop_reason\":\"tool_use\",\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":2719,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":0,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":0,\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":0,\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":0},\"output_tokens\":392,\"