            "size": 1613,
            "text": "{\"model\":\"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001\",\"id\":\"msg_01J9Ek4XvJSfywUcZJtAddA9\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"id\":\"toolu_01N9QUVuGPLE3Juqzcbm4QGb\",\"name\":\"extract-61\",\"input\":{\"type\":\"reply\",\"text\":\"I love the concept! \\\"Friend of the Pod\\\" is a catchy name. But I need to dig deeper to understand what makes this truly compelling.\\n\\nLet me ask you this: **What specific problem does your podcast matchmaking service solve?** And **who are you solving it for?**\\n\\nFor example, are you helping:\\n- Podcast hosts find guests who can drive engagement?\\n- Guests find the right podcasts to appear on?\\n- Both?\\n\\nAnd what makes your matchmaking service different from just searching through podcast directories or using LinkedIn?\",\"examples\":[\"A service that connects B2B SaaS founders with niche podcasts in their industry so they can reach their ideal customers through authentic conversations\",\"A platform that matches emerging musicians with podcast hosts looking for indie artists to interview, solving the discovery problem for both sides\",\"An AI-powered service that matches thought leaders with podcasts that align with their expertise and audience, saving them hours of research\"],\"conclusion\":\"Help me understand the core problem you're solving and who benefits most. That's the foundation of everything else.\"}}],\"stop_reason\":\"tool_use\",\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":2719,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":0,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":0,\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":0,\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":0},\"output_tokens\":307,\"service_tier\":\"standard\"}}"
